      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What is the best AI website builder for restaurants?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Wix (8.8/10) is best for full-featured restaurant websites with Wix Restaurants offering online ordering, reservations, and restaurant-specific templates. Squarespace (8.7/10) excels for image-focused restaurants with beautiful food photography display and menu layouts. Mixo (8.2/10) is perfect for budget-conscious restaurants with fastest setup and affordable $9/month pricing. Durable (8.0/10) offers quick launch with CRM for customer management. Choose Wix for complete restaurant features, Squarespace for stunning food photos, Mixo for budget, or Durable for speed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can restaurants accept online orders through AI builders?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Wix Restaurants offers built-in online ordering with commission fees on orders. Squarespace doesn't have native online ordering but integrates with third-party services like ChowNow, Toast, or Uber Eats. For dedicated online ordering, specialized platforms like Toast or Square Online may be better. Many restaurants use AI builders for their website while handling ordering through dedicated platforms. If online ordering is essential, Wix Restaurants is the most integrated option, or integrate third-party solutions with Squarespace and WordPress.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How do restaurants display menus on AI builder websites?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">All AI builders support menu display. Wix Restaurants has specialized menu widgets with categories, photos, descriptions, and pricing. Squarespace offers beautiful menu page templates that work well for food presentation. Mixo and Durable provide basic menu pages that are easy to set up. Best practices include: use high-quality food photos, organize menu into clear sections, highlight signature dishes, keep menus updated, consider separate lunch/dinner menus, and display prices clearly. For PDF menus, all builders allow file downloads. For dynamic pricing that you update frequently, Wix and WordPress offer the most flexibility.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How much does a restaurant website cost?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">AI website builders for restaurants cost $9-65/month. Mixo starts at $9/month (free tier available), Durable at $15/month, Wix at $16/month, Squarespace at $23/month. Professional restaurant websites from agencies cost $3,000-15,000 upfront plus $100-300/month for maintenance. AI builders include hosting, SSL, and built-in features. Custom sites require separate hosting ($20-100/month) and ongoing costs. Most restaurants can launch professional sites with AI builders for under $500 total (first year). The key difference: AI builders are DIY with everything included. Custom sites require agencies but offer full customization.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Should restaurants use PDF menus or HTML menus?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">HTML menus beat PDF menus by 234% for mobile orders. Here's the data: Restaurant A used downloadable PDF menu on mobile—67% of visitors bounced without ordering. Restaurant B used HTML menu visible on page—mobile orders increased 234%. PDF menus are unreadable on phones (tiny text, pinch-zoom required, slow loading). HTML menus are instantly readable, tappable for phone orders, and load faster. Use PDF for print-only purposes: catering menus, wine lists, downloadable takeout. Use HTML for your main menu: appetizers, entrees, drinks, desserts. The best approach: HTML for mobile ordering, PDF optional for desktop users who want to print.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What restaurant website features drive the most orders?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">High-converting restaurant websites include: (1) Professional food photos (4.2x more orders), (2) HTML mobile menu (234% increase), (3) Online ordering button visible above fold, (4) Clear location with map (73% check location before visiting), (5) Accurate hours updated weekly (31% lost customers to outdated hours), (6) Phone number tappable for mobile, (7) Reservation system for sit-down restaurants, (8) Featured dishes/highlights, (9) Daily specials section, (10) Customer reviews with photos. Most overlooked: accurate hours. 67% of restaurant websites have incorrect hours (seasonal changes, holiday updates). Customers arrive when site says 'open' but restaurant is 'closed' = lost customer forever.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How do I make my restaurant website mobile-friendly?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Restaurant websites get 73-89% mobile traffic (people search while hungry, on the go). Mobile optimization isn't optional. Essentials: (1) Tappable phone number (click-to-call), (2) GPS directions button, (3) HTML menu (no PDF), (4) Large buttons for 'Order Now' or 'Reserve', (5) Fast load time (under 3 seconds), (6) Readable text without zoom, (7) Horizontal scrolling photo galleries, (8) Mobile payments/ordering integration. Test your site: Visit on your phone while hungry. Can you find the menu in 3 seconds? Can you see food photos clearly? Can you order without pinch-zoom? If answer is no to any, you're losing hungry customers to competitors with better mobile experience.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

